# RASCAL - Mobile App Communication Protocol

## 📡 Overview

This document describes the complete communication protocol between the mobile app (via Bluetooth) and the RASCAL robot's Arduino controller.

**Protocol Type:** Serial text-based (ASCII)  
**Transport:** Bluetooth Classic (HC-05) via UART  
**Baud Rate:** 9600 bps  
**Line Ending:** Newline (`\n`)  
**Direction:** Bidirectional

---

## 📤 Command Structure (Phone → Robot)

### Format
```
COMMAND[\n]
```
or
```
COMMAND:PARAMETER[\n]
```

- **Case Sensitive:** Commands should be UPPERCASE
- **Delimiter:** Colon (`:`) separates command from parameters
- **Terminator:** Newline character (`\n`) ends each command
- **Encoding:** ASCII text

---

## 📝 Command Reference

### 1. Motion Commands

#### FWD - Move Forward
```
FWD[\n]
```
**Description:** Move robot forward at BASE_SPEED  
**Parameters:** None  
**Mode Change:** Switches to MANUAL mode  
**Duration:** Continuous until new command  
**Response:** None (see status updates)

**Example:**
```
Send: FWD
```

---

#### BWD - Move Backward
```
BWD[\n]
```
**Description:** Move robot backward at BASE_SPEED  
**Parameters:** None  
**Mode Change:** Switches to MANUAL mode  

**Example:**
```
Send: BWD
```

---

#### LEFT - Turn Left
```
LEFT[\n]
```
**Description:** Rotate robot counterclockwise (tank turn)  
**Parameters:** None  
**Mode Change:** Switches to MANUAL mode  
**Turn Type:** In-place rotation (left wheels backward, right forward)

**Example:**
```
Send: LEFT
```

---

#### RIGHT - Turn Right
```
RIGHT[\n]
```
**Description:** Rotate robot clockwise (tank turn)  
**Parameters:** None  
**Mode Change:** Switches to MANUAL mode  

**Example:**
```
Send: RIGHT
```

---

#### STOP - Stop All Motors
```
STOP[\n]
```
**Description:** Immediately halt all motors  
**Parameters:** None  
**Mode Change:** Switches to STOPPED mode  
**Use Case:** Emergency stop, end of manual control

**Example:**
```
Send: STOP
```

---

### 2. Autonomous Navigation Commands

#### GOTO - Set Waypoint and Navigate
```
GOTO:LATITUDE,LONGITUDE[\n]
```
**Description:** Set target GPS coordinates and begin autonomous navigation  
**Parameters:**  
- `LATITUDE`: Decimal degrees (e.g., 37.774929)
- `LONGITUDE`: Decimal degrees (e.g., -122.419416)

**Mode Change:** Switches to AUTONOMOUS mode  
**Response:** `WAYPOINT:SET`  
**Completion:** `WAYPOINT:REACHED` when within threshold

**Example:**
```
Send: GOTO:37.774929,-122.419416
Receive: WAYPOINT:SET
[Robot navigates...]
Receive: WAYPOINT:REACHED
```

**Coordinate Format:**
- Use decimal degrees (DD.dddddd)
- Latitude range: -90.0 to 90.0
- Longitude range: -180.0 to 180.0
- Precision: 6 decimal places recommended (~0.1m accuracy)

**Getting Coordinates:**
- Google Maps: Right-click → Coordinates
- GPS app: Long-press on map
- Online: https://www.latlong.net

---

#### CLEAR - Cancel Waypoint
```
CLEAR[\n]
```
**Description:** Cancel autonomous navigation and stop  
**Parameters:** None  
**Mode Change:** Switches to STOPPED mode  
**Response:** `WAYPOINT:CLEARED`

**Example:**
```
Send: CLEAR
Receive: WAYPOINT:CLEARED
```

---

### 3. Status & Configuration Commands

#### POS - Request Position & Status
```
POS[\n]
```
**Description:** Request immediate status update  
**Parameters:** None  
**Response:** Full STATUS message (see below)

**Example:**
```
Send: POS
Receive: STATUS:MANUAL|37.774929,-122.419416|SAT:8|HDG:245.3
```

---

#### SPEED - Adjust Motor Speed
```
SPEED:VALUE[\n]
```
**Description:** Change base motor speed  
**Parameters:**  
- `VALUE`: Integer 0-255 (PWM duty cycle)
  - 0 = stopped
  - 128 = 50% power
  - 255 = 100% power

**Response:** `SPEED:SET:VALUE`  
**Note:** Current implementation acknowledges but may not persist

**Example:**
```
Send: SPEED:220
Receive: SPEED:SET:220
```

---

## 📥 Response Structure (Robot → Phone)

### Format
```
TYPE:DATA1|DATA2|DATA3[\n]
```

- **Delimiter:** Pipe (`|`) separates data fields
- **Terminator:** Newline character (`\n`)

---

## 📨 Response Messages

### Startup Message
```
RASCAL:READY[\n]
```
**When:** Sent immediately after Arduino powers on  
**Purpose:** Indicates robot is initialized and ready for commands

---

### Waypoint Responses

#### Waypoint Set Confirmation
```
WAYPOINT:SET[\n]
```
**When:** After valid GOTO command received

#### Waypoint Reached
```
WAYPOINT:REACHED[\n]
```
**When:** Robot arrives within WAYPOINT_THRESHOLD (default 3m) of target

#### Waypoint Cleared
```
WAYPOINT:CLEARED[\n]
```
**When:** After CLEAR command received

---

### Status Update (Periodic)
```
STATUS:MODE|POSITION|SATELLITES|HEADING[|WAYPOINT|DISTANCE][\n]
```

**Frequency:** Every 2 seconds (automatic)  
**Also sent:** In response to POS command

#### Fields:

1. **MODE**
   - `MANUAL` - Under direct Bluetooth control
   - `AUTO` - Autonomous navigation active
   - `STOPPED` - Motors off, idle

2. **POSITION**
   - Format: `LAT,LON` (decimal degrees)
   - Example: `37.774929,-122.419416`
   - Special: `NO_GPS` if no valid fix

3. **SATELLITES**
   - Format: `SAT:N`
   - N = number of satellites in use
   - Example: `SAT:8`
   - Minimum for fix: 4
   - Good fix: 8+

4. **HEADING**
   - Format: `HDG:DEG`
   - DEG = heading in degrees (0-360)
   - Example: `HDG:245.3`
   - 0° = North, 90° = East, 180° = South, 270° = West

5. **WAYPOINT** (only in AUTONOMOUS mode)
   - Format: `WP:LAT,LON`
   - Target coordinates
   - Example: `WP:37.775000,-122.420000`

6. **DISTANCE** (only in AUTONOMOUS mode)
   - Format: `DIST:M`
   - Distance to waypoint in meters
   - Example: `DIST:15.7`

#### Complete Examples:

**Manual Mode:**
```
STATUS:MANUAL|37.774929,-122.419416|SAT:8|HDG:245.3
```

**Autonomous Mode:**
```
STATUS:AUTO|37.774929,-122.419416|SAT:10|HDG:32.1|WP:37.775000,-122.420000|DIST:8.3
```

**No GPS Fix:**
```
STATUS:STOPPED|NO_GPS|SAT:0|HDG:0.0
```

