### Example 2: Autonomous Delivery

```
Phone                    Robot
  |                        |
  |--- POS ----------------|  (Get current position)
  |                        |
  |<--- STATUS:STOPPED|37.7749,-122.4194|...
  |                        |
  |--- GOTO:37.7750,-122.4195
  |                        |
  |<--- WAYPOINT:SET ------|
  |                        |... navigating
  |                        |
  |<--- STATUS:AUTO|37.7749,-122.4194|...|DIST:10.2
  |                        |... navigating
  |<--- STATUS:AUTO|37.7749,-122.4195|...|DIST:5.1
  |                        |... navigating
  |<--- STATUS:AUTO|37.7750,-122.4195|...|DIST:1.2
  |                        |... arrived
  |<--- WAYPOINT:REACHED --|
  |                        |
```

### Example 3: Multi-Waypoint Route

```python
# Pseudocode for sequential waypoints

waypoints = [
    (37.7749, -122.4194),
    (37.7751, -122.4196),
    (37.7753, -122.4198)
]

for lat, lon in waypoints:
    send(f"GOTO:{lat},{lon}")
    
    # Wait for confirmation
    response = wait_for_message()
    if response != "WAYPOINT:SET":
        print("Error setting waypoint")
        break
    
    # Wait for arrival
    while True:
        msg = wait_for_message()
        if msg == "WAYPOINT:REACHED":
            print(f"Reached waypoint {lat},{lon}")
            break
        elif "STATUS:AUTO" in msg:
            # Parse distance
            dist = parse_distance(msg)
            print(f"Distance remaining: {dist}m")

print("Delivery complete!")
```

